headline: CVS Stock Is Rising. A Wall Street Upgrade Helps Keep the Momentum Going.
summary: Shares of  CVS Health  were rising Thursday after the company notched an upgrade on Wall Street as it continues a monthslong bull run.  Analysts at Baird upgraded the stock to Outperform from Neutral and lifted their target to $82 from $71.  The firm has growing confidence in the turnaround story of CVS’s health insurance business.
